{
  "text": "The question as to what are the causes for a disrupted clock is not yet completely answered, although promising candidates have been identified. These vary from external factors like night shift work, variations of day length, melatonin release, exposure to artificial light and to low frequency electromagnetic waves, dietary factors, to internal deregulations at the cellular level, regarding genetic disorders in clock or clockregulating genes [CITATION_1] .",
